<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="535" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–1049</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mao Tse-tung</persName> to the
                            Appointed Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Yenan</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-16">16 December, 1944</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear General Hurley</hi>: Thank you very much for your
                        kind letter.<note n="98" xml:id="d535fn98">Dated November 10, <ref target="#pg_689">p. 689</ref>.</note>
                    </p>
                    <pb facs="0755" n="741" xml:id="pg_741"/>
                    <p>Last November when President Roosevelt was reelected, I sent him a note of
                        congratulations. In his reply,<note n="99" xml:id="d535fn99">Not
                            printed.</note> he said that for the defeat of Japanese aggression, he
                        was willing to cooperate with all anti-Japanese forces in China. Please tell
                        your President that I subscribe fully to his policy and that I thank
                        him.</p>
                    <p>This letter is transmitted to you through the kindness of Colonel Barrett
                        whom we hope will soon return to Yenan.</p>
                    <p>Several other points which I would like to take up with you have been covered
                        by General Chou En-lai in his letter.<note n="1" xml:id="d535fn1">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                        </note>
                    </p>
                    <p>With best wishes,</p>
                    <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mao Tse Tung</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>